caption: As a recent bride who got married at Celeste and a Wedding Planner by trade, I highly suggest Celeste for your venue, no matter the type of event! The team is incredibly easy to work with, the service is next-level (guests are still commenting about how well taken care of they felt), the food is PHENOMENAL, and the spaces are absolutely STUNNING! Kelsey, Cassie and the rest of the team brought us so much joy on our wedding day thanks to all of their hard work , and we could not be more grateful for the fabulous experience from start to finish! <3

Look the food and drinks are fine but if you make a reservation and request rooftop. You’re not going to get it. They’re reserved already. Especially on Thursday even if you request rooftop a month in advance for your 30th birthday lol. I was specifically instructed by the host Alex to request my reservation for rooftop. Did it twice and still nothing. On top of that Alex told us there’s a two hour limit bc of covid which is understandable but this rule doesn’t apply to the guests on the rooftop. They can stay as long as they want so we can’t wait out their reservation. Never coming back
The CUTEST atmosphere and great apps!
This place is great

A cool place to gather with friends over drinks. The music wasn't so great on our floor but nice to gather especially before exploring Hubbard street. The cool cucumber drink is bomb and the scallops were cooked well.
Great customer service!! Wonderful vibes😊😊 And the fried Chicken is definitely on point!! If you looking for a chill vibe with your Boo this is the place to go..

Rip off warning! Called for reservation, was told to wait in line and then was kicked out of line and not being given a reason to why I was told to leave. While I ended up getting in, it’s nothing special for the price, some locals but tourist based and no one working their is happy. For the price there’s many other better venues and unique atmosphere. The light up floor is kinda cool, but seems dated and was worn out like most of the club. Although Chicago isn’t what it used to be, it went from the clean New York with better architecture, to mainly angry people and the friendly vibe is their, but it’s no what it used to be

And the manager didn’t want to exchange the bottle, the steak was ordered medium cooked, came pretty much well done and no taste, the burger and pasta had human hair. Mezcal Hell. They made a custom cocktail to meet my desires. Amazing and personal service. I said I would line X Y AND Z  in my cocktail and they made it. Perfect.
Really cozy place, great drinks and amazing pasta!

I had the opportunity of visiting here the past weekend with my husband. Although, we were not able to be sitted inside because we didn't have a reservation, we were able to grab a table outside. We had a couple of drinks, truffle fries and steak sliders, both dishes were really good. I have to say I wasn't impressed by the drinks we had. Also, the main reason for the 3 🌟 is because our waitress was very nonchalant and we had to keep letting several other workers know what we wanted or if they could find our waitress so we could be helped. She even bought an extra drink to my husband that we did not order, but had inquired about. I thought that was very rude and unprofessional, you shouldn't assume things like that especially when we're being charged for it. When asked about it, she said "sure you ordered it remember when you asked me about what's in it" and she walked away, didn't even give us a chance to respond. Totally not cool. I asked about several menu items as well but she didn't bring those over!

My review is with respect to the bar area. This is my go to spot for drinks in River North. Classy and Chic. You can have a conversation and can enjoy some great drinks. Rooftop is really pretty too. Highly recommended.
Closed during posted open hours.
My sister got married on the roof. It was truly magical, the food was absolutely amazing, although there was no elevator to the fourth floor.

I lost my entire purse when I was there. I was surprised at how kind the manager was about my situation. She took down my number and email in case she found it. She was so gracious and she ended up finding my purse and facilitated it being picked up by my friend. Such a fun club with different vibes on each floor and great management!
Fun place with each floor having a different vibe
Open space at the rail on a Tuesday.... downtown....open late... Run it bro!!!
Went to a 24hr wedding. The food was great. After 11pm. Time to get your groove on. Check out!
The service here was pretty bad (forgot reservation, made us wait to sit, slow service). My steak ordered rare was well done. Three stars are for the friendly staff, fun atmosphere, and cocktails.
Super fun club, with a lot if options. Cocktail bar downstairs, lounges/restaurant upstairs, and a dance floor on the 3rd floor!

If you just so happen to not be the preferred demographic they cater to, expect them to suddenly enforce their STRICT dress code of “no gym shoes or sneakers”, while simultaneously letting everyone of the preferred demographic inside, barely even glancing at them.

I’m an often guest of Celeste! Have been going for years. Absolutely love the place. Except for my last experience. My friends and I were asked to leave with no explanation. One of the security guys came  to my group of friends and escorted us out directly after we ordered a set of drinks. We were to ourselves and were dancing to the music. Then got asked to leave “per management” and “per management” didn’t give us a reason as to why. Management refused to speak to us and give us an explanation as to why we were asked to leave. At this point I have a feeling our race has something to do with it as we did not do anything out of line. Our actions and character was with the energy and flow of the crowd and we were singled out to leave. Although I absolutely love this place and have been going for years... throwing parties, enjoying dinners and nights here... I will never be going here again after that experience. I guess this is a place in river north that singles people out according to race. Get it together Celeste. It’s 2020

Love everything about Celeste! Super fun spot for drinks and food. Also in a lively part of town. I had a Cucumber Collins cocktail and truffle fries—the best of the best. It gets slammed, though. Private parties can rent out certain floors, so make sure to call beforehand and ask which floors are open or, if there is a private party, what time it will be over. It’s so worth it!
Pretty dope place for the weekend. Expect expensive drinks and rude people tryna cut in line for the bartender

Waste of time!  Flew down from Texas to celebrate my brother’s birthday with a group of 9 people. We got there early and we were ready to buy drinks all night long. The bouncer told us that we didn’t allow hoodies inside. I had a dress shirt and dress shoes underneath my zipper hoodie. It’s 32 degrees outside. Plus, they never had a dress code before according to my brother and his friends. Save your money.
The hostess forgot about us, but once we reminded her we were in need of a menu service was good.

I wish there was an option to give negative stars. This is one of the many racist places on Hubbard street. The guy on the entrance didn't let us in saying they only accept reservations while he let all the white people behind us (we did checked with couple of them and they did not have a reservation). When we tried to have a conversation with the guy for his behaviour he started behaving rudely and asked us to leave his property. Avoid this place (or in general any bar on Hubbard street) if you have brown skin.

First time here - don't normally frequent bars/restos in River North, but wanted to leave a review b/c the bartenders are super kind & low key - courteous, attentive, lovely! Gin-forward cocktail menu, truffle fries were great (but not the aioli) & skip the brussels sprouts...good flavor w/ parmesan, but slightly overdone and pancetta was just salty hard nuggets that didn't add anything to the dish. Honestly surprised by how small the space is - 4 floors but all 4 spaces are quite narrow. Disco was fun, to be expected Saturday night crowd

The Food was great,  But I will complain that I was scolded by the host that I need to wear better/nicer looking clothes. I looked on the website and can't seem to find a dress code. So Im furious that they wouldn't let me in until they found out I was with a small party.  Yes still proceeded to tell me next time to dress better.

Great music, fine cocktails and surprisngly delicious snacks. Celeste is a popular spot in River North with a great vibe to it. The music could be a little too loud to talk in you are in a larger group. Happy hours Tue-Fri 5-8p is something that's hard to beat. Moreover, this place is open till 4am so you never have to worry about closing the tap if you are having a great night.

I Shazamed so many songs here because they know how to set the vibes! The top floor garden bar area was awesome to chat and drink in. But the third floor disco, is like out of a movie. This place should totally be checked out.
So amazing!!! The best nightclub in the River North District by far.
I have tried many times to get in contact with the management because I was discriminated inside by the black guy at the door. He attacked me for being transgender and I didn't even know him!

Each level of Celeste has a totally different vibe. Top floor is a disco club, which is fun, but the floors are really slick and people wipe out pretty regularly. The downstairs bar is a cocktail bar, which is much more my speed, and it is very nice. Great cocktails and a fun atmosphere.

This place is great for a rehearsal dinner!  We had originally booked elsewhere and got bullied out of the space a few weeks before our wedding, but Celeste was there to save the day at the last minute.  They provided amazing atmosphere/decor, delicious food and drinks, extremely fast service, and made the entire process easy and smooth from start to finish.  We were also able to rent a TV and microphone for speakers/slideshows during the rehearsal dinner, which was a nice addition.  After dinner, most people ended up downstairs at Disco for some more drinks and dancing.  A perfect night.  Highly recommend Celeste to anyone planning an event.  Thank you!
I found one the best burger in Chicago there. The price is good for such a good burger.

Fabulous place. We attended a private party, then went upstairs to dance, then went downstairs for some food. I loved it all. Beautiful decor, great dance floor, good food, great vibe

It is a great looking bar with okayish drinks but delicious food.  I was disappointed by the two drinks I ordered so did not order a third.  The food itself is worth a stop.  The look is chic and the staff friendly

The truffle fries were delicious but sliders and cocktails lacked much in way of presentation or unique flavors.  What bothered me most about my experience here was when our waitress added a charge for a small cup of aioli without informing us. In hindsight this seems very stingy.

Made a reservation at this place to celebrate my brother’s birthday because we thought it looked like a great place. Upon arriving the hostess was not present, and we were confused as to where to go to sit or find out where we should wait. She finally showed up and showed us to our table which was still dirty from the past reservation. It got cleaned after a few minutes, but there were still some coats sitting on the edge of the booth. We sat down to start looking at the menu, and a member of my group moved the coats from the edge of the booth to the corner so we wouldn’t sit on them. They slipped off of the back of the booth and the hostess happened to be walking by. She accused my friend of throwing the coats onto her on purpose. We calmly told her we would never mean to do that on purpose, but this hostess was so riled up she accused us of threatening her to the point that she felt unsafe. Management came over to our table and as a surprise to us, instead of apologizing we were further accused of harassing their hostess. This place is ridiculous and we left immediately after being confronted by multiple employees. We would have paid good money as a group of 6 and are extremely turned off and disappointed by this horrendous accusation. I do not recommend going here.

One of the coolest night spots in downtown Chicago. It has 4 floors all with distinct vibes. The bottom floor is your typical cocktail bar with something for anyone. The 2nd floor is more tables and kind of a social dining/drinking experience. The 3rd floor has a light up dance floor and a disco vibe. The 4th floor has a bunch of plants and a jungle vibe. I've been here when entire floors are closed so it's sort of hit or miss and they do charge cover on weekends sometimes but it's one of the coolest spots for sure in Chicago to club or drink.

This place is Fun! 4 levels of fun. It is definitely more loungy (not a real word,  I know, but apropo.) Really lovely drinks,  great music and overall cool vibe. The other thing I really enjoyed was that each level has its own vibe,  decor,  music and energy. The top floor was my fave. It felt like a rich,  fluorescent fairy forest. I wanted to stay there the whole night,  but hubby had a tab at lower level. We didn't check if they were transferable. We'll for sure be going back soon. Oh,  in case you're up for a hardy party, the 3rd floor has a completely lit up dance floor with very dancy DJ music. It's pretty trippy,  but exciting. It made me think that this world be great for groups of my friends and I to go out and dance together.

If I could give no stars TRUST ME I would. I'm here attempting to enjoy my evening because I had a long chaotic work week and was forced to get up from my seat on the "rooftop" without a view because a group of European males wanted our seats. Myself as well as my guests were enjoying our too sweet gimlets and waiting on our food to arrive and the tight pants wearing bouncer said "I'm sorry but you have to get up because someone bought these seats right now". Imagine how I felt when that was said to us. I looked around and there was NO reserved sign on the table or near the seats we were sitting in and there were other European females sitting across from us, why weren't they asked to move?? It they wanted us, the African Americans to get up.  I am SICK AND TIRED of the racism not only in this country but at  this restaurant because this isn't the first time I received service from this establishment that wasn't up to par.  Words can not describe how disappointed I am right now and unfortunately I won't be back to enjoy some of the best fried chicken in the city. Its really sad that my Black Dollars aren't welcomed.

I really like Celeste overall. It's a great spot to come to during the week because of the happy hour and each floor is a unique experience. The first and second floors are good for a low key vibes and the disco floor is awesome for dancing. I'd really recommend coming here during off-hours though since Friday and Saturday nights is really challenging to get in. Make sure you make it to the Disco though since it's truly like not other bar in Chicago. You'll have a blast!

I find it funny how bartenders expect a minimum of 20% no matter what they do. Sorry, I only tip 20% if you have been going out of your way to provide me with top quality service. It is very convenient to drink a little one floor below the bar and then head up to do some dancing (cool disco theme too!).  However, my disappointment stems from the fact that I had made a reservation for the upstairs Victorian garden area and upon arrival was kicked out of seats labeled "reserved". I explained I had a reservation and they proceeded to send me on a wild goose chase through the bar talking to multiple people. I'm no fool and realized what they were doing. Typical bar/club doorman behavior.  Ideal Experience: Grab drinks before, get here before 10 and take advantage of the dance floor early and then move on. Don't drink too much here or your wallet will be sad. I had high hopes, but it's a long fall from grace.  My friends and I visited Celeste/Disco on a Saturday night. After ordering drinks from the bartender, we waited 25 minutes for him to serve 5-6 other customers before making our drinks (even though it wasn't crowded). Later, when I received the bill, my card was not on it and I tried to get his attention, but he acted like he had given it to me already. I realized later that he stole my card.  I also went inside Disco and had left to go the bathroom. When I returned, security refused me entry, stating that he had only let in "three black girls and I wasn't one of them." He said that I was welcome to go to the rooftop. We went to the rooftop, where we were personally assigned security to watch us while we were there.  The black male security guard, later asked us to "get our stuff" and leave, despite the fact that I hadn't done anything inappropriate. Embarrassed, we complied without hostility and descended the stairs to the exit, passing a crowd of people. My best friend, who is white, noticed that the security made an effort to stand between her and myself, to make it appear that he was only kicking the black women out.  There are many great examples of inclusive places in River North. This place is not one of them. I wouldn't recommend this place to my worst enemy, based on the treatment that we received.
